{
  "texts": [
    "These interests are typically predicted on the basis of the users' online habits and previous choices.",
    "If one focuses exclusively on the hazard component, these systems do not strike as particularly risky, especially when compared with systems whose failure can result in human victims.",
    "However, things change when the component of exposure is considered.",
    "Due to their being pervasive in online environments, including extremely popular platforms, recommender systems virtually monitor and influence the behaviour of all users.",
    "As a result, all the possible concerns about privacy, addiction, and manipulation apply on a massive scale."
  ]
}